    <text type="letter">
        <body><pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc.02852.001_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline> 
                    <date when="1876-12-11" rend="right"><choice><abbr>Dec</abbr><expan>December</expan></choice> 11 '76</date>
                </dateline>
                <salute>My dear Linton</salute>
            </opener>
            <p>I have been for some weeks down in the country&#8212;half moping like&#8212;yet 
                feeling <hi rend="underline">rather better</hi>
                these days, upon the whole&#8212;Your note of some weeks since<ptr target="n5002d"/> ought to have 
                been answered before. I have been waiting for the chance to get from the
                bindery, or from my stack, (as I unwrap the books) a copy of 
                <hi rend="underline">Two Rivulets</hi><ptr target="loc.02250_n7"/> 
                <hi rend="underline">with the dark brown</hi> label
                you want&#8212;I have it in mind, &#38; shall get it so, &#38; send it you&#8212;                
                <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="loc.02852.002_large.jpg" type="verso"/>
                Meantime, let this remorseful note be my apology&#8212;</p> 
            <p>&#8212;My address here is still the same&#8212;</p>
            <closer>
                <signed>Walt Whitman</signed>
                <address>
                    <addrLine><name>Camden</name></addrLine>
                    <addrLine><name>New Jersey</name></addrLine>
                </address>
            </closer>
        </body>
    </text>
